body:
I made a script to synchronize also the folders so that it will become an exact copy, so now it is usable for me. If anybody is interested the PHP script I made is below. It is not very efficient in getting the folders deleted but it gets the job done.

_How to use it:_
* Install PHP if it is not already installed (`sudo apt-get install php5` on Linux/Debian)
* Save the above script to file (eg. `dirs_cleanup.php`)
* Modify the settings in the top of the file
* Run the script: `php dirs_cleanup.php`. It is safe to do this, it doesn't delete anything. It generates a bash script with rclone commands which you can check yourself before you run it afterwards.

```php
<?php
// SETTINGS:
$remote_path = 'YourRemoteName:/var-www/';
$remote_extraflags = '';
$local_path  = '/var/www/';
$local_extraflags = '--exclude=cache/**';

// ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
$temp_folder = '/tmp/';  //folder to store temporary files in

echo '---- REMOTE LISTING ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------'. PHP_EOL;
$exitcode = null;
passthru('rclone lsjson "'. $remote_path .'" --no-modtime --recursive '. $remote_extraflags .' | tee '. $temp_folder .'filelist_remote.json', $exitcode);
if ($exitcode !== 0) {
	die('Creating file list on remote failed with exit code '. $exitcode);
}
echo '------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------'. PHP_EOL;

echo '---- LOCAL LISTING -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------'. PHP_EOL;
$exitcode = null;
passthru('rclone lsjson "'. $local_path  .'" --no-modtime --recursive '. $local_extraflags  .' | tee '. $temp_folder .'filelist_local.json',  $exitcode);
if ($exitcode !== 0) {
	die('Creating file list on remote failed with exit code '. $exitcode);
}
echo '------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------'. PHP_EOL;

$filelist_local  = file_get_contents($temp_folder .'filelist_local.json');
$filelist_remote = file_get_contents($temp_folder .'filelist_remote.json');

$filelist_local  = json_decode($filelist_local,  false);
$filelist_remote = json_decode($filelist_remote, false);

$local_folders = [];
foreach ($filelist_local as $dir) {
	if ($dir->IsDir) {
		$local_folders[] = $dir->Path;
	}
}


echo '---- DIRS TO DELETE ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------'. PHP_EOL;
$all_commands = [];
foreach ($filelist_remote as $dir) {
	if ($dir->IsDir) {
		if (!in_array($dir->Path, $local_folders, true)) {
			$fullpath = rtrim($remote_path, '/') .'/'. $dir->Path;
			$delete_cmd = 'rclone rmdir "'. $fullpath .'" -v'. PHP_EOL;
			$all_commands[] = $delete_cmd;
			echo $delete_cmd;
		}
	}
}
rsort($all_commands);  //so that child folders are deleted before parent folders

echo PHP_EOL;
echo count($all_commands) .' directories to be deleted.'. PHP_EOL;

if (!empty($all_commands)) {
	file_put_contents('dirs_to_delete.sh', '#!/bin/bash'. PHP_EOL . implode('', $all_commands));
	echo 'Run `bash dirs_to_delete.sh` to perform the deletion.'. PHP_EOL;
} else {
	@unlink('dirs_to_delete.sh');
}
```
